Elements.Description: When I haven't been able to smoke for a few hours, the craving gets intolerable.
I find myself reaching for cigarettes without thinking about it.
I drop everything to go out and buy cigarettes.
I smoke more before going into a situation where smoking is not allowed.
I crave cigarettes at certain times of day.
When I'm really craving a cigarette, it feels like I'm in the grip of some unknown force that I cannot control.
My urges to smoke keep getting stronger if I don't smoke.
After not smoking for a while, I need to smoke in order to avoid feeling any discomfort.
My desire to smoke seems overpowering.
Cravings for a cigarette make it difficult for me to quit.
It is hard to ignore urges to smoke.
When I go without a cigarette for a few hours, I experience craving.
The idea of not having any cigarettes causes me stress.
When I run out of cigarettes, I find it almost unbearable.
I get a real gnawing hunger for a cigarette when l haven't smoked in a while.
I smoke even when I am so ill that I am in bed most of the day.
When I go too long without a cigarette I feel impatient.
When I go too long without a cigarette I get strong urges that are hard to get rid of.
It is hard for me to go without smoking for a whole day.
Smoking is a large part of my daily life.
I am tempted to smoke when I realize I haven't smoked for a while.
I become more addicted the more I smoke.
I feel like I smoke all the time.
I would go crazy if I couldn't smoke.
If I quit smoking I will experience intense cravings for a cigarette.
My life is full of reminders to smoke.
